  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Operational Action Plan the Integration of a Sustainable Development Perspective into the implementation of the Objectives of the World Heritage Convention in Africa</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Following the 2nd Cycle of the Periodic Reporting exercise in the Africa Region and since 2017 focusing on bridging the gap towards new activities, the Secretariat will focus on carrying out the 3rd cycle and a new regional Action Plan from 2022. The action plan with related activities will address conservation, protection and management of WH sites by focussing in conflict and post-conflict situations, challenges such as climate change, urbanization, youth employment, community involvement and gender equality, taking into account the outcome of the International Conference &quot;Safeguarding African World Heritage as a Driver of Sustainable Development&quot; and the operationalization of the Policy Document for the Integration of a SD Perspective into the Processes of the World Heritage Convention.</narrative>
  </description>
